 They then reality-tested their model by bouncing their ideas off hundreds of managers who were living change on a day-to-day basis. Those ideas are collected in this practical book, which will be of use to anyone who is likely to lead change initiatives in almost any organizational environment—from executives, to consultants, to management students.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 31. Jan 2022) 4aBusiness -- Management and Leadership. 4aBusiness -- Organizational Development and Change. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Leadership.2bisacsh1 aFedor, Donald B., eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080476316540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804763165423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780804763165/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles